                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79620 Boeing Airplane Co./39: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-09T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1929—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. Your 7, January 8, 5 p.m. Inasmuch as the time was too short to obtain
                    ratification of contract by Executive prior to end of Alvear term it was thought
                    safer to inaugurate fresh negotiations with the new administration. These are
                    not concluded yet, the main point of discussion being method of reimbursing
                    company. O’Neil’s representative seems to be confident as to ultimate
                        prospects<note n="14" xml:id="d676fn14">A decree granting Tri-Motors Airways
                        the right to establish an air service with the United States was signed Feb.
                        28, 1929. The decree embodying the contract was printed in the Buenos Aires
                            <hi rend="italic">La Epoca</hi>, Feb. 28, 1929. (File No. 811.79620
                        Boeing Airplane Co./41, 42.)</note> but by reason of recent change of
                    administration Government business is subject to delay. Commercial attaché also
                    cabling.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
